{%- assign mail = settings.contact_email | default: shop.email -%}
{%- assign sg_full = settings.size_guide_diagram_full -%}
{%- assign sg_chest = settings.size_guide_img_chest -%}
{%- assign sg_waist = settings.size_guide_img_waist -%}
{%- assign sg_hips = settings.size_guide_img_hips -%}
{%- assign sg_any = false -%}
{%- if sg_full != blank or sg_chest != blank or sg_waist != blank or sg_hips != blank -%}
  {%- assign sg_any = true -%}
{%- endif -%}
<div class="prose rte">
  {%- if request.design_mode and sg_any == false -%}
    <p
      class="size-guide-admin-hint"
      style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;background:#f4f0eb;border-radius:10px;font-size:0.9rem;margin-bottom:1rem;"
    >
      <strong>Size guide images:</strong>
      Theme settings → Brand &amp; contact → scroll to
      <strong>Size guide — diagrams</strong>
      and upload images, then Save.
    </p>
  {%- endif -%}

  <p>
    We are obsessed with fit and want you to feel your best, no matter what you’re dressing for. Every style is perfected by our in-house garment tech team until we’re happy that each seam sits exactly right. Our product pages include specific sizing information; the following is a general guide. If you need further assistance, email
    <a href="mailto:{{ mail | escape }}">Customer Care</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Glazur size guide</h2>
  <p>
    To ensure each piece fits beautifully and you feel confident and comfortable, please take your measurements carefully. Use a soft measuring tape and avoid pulling too tightly.
  </p>

  {%- if sg_full != blank -%}
    {%- assign sg_full_alt = sg_full.alt | default: 'How to measure — size diagram' -%}
    <figure class="size-guide-visual size-guide-visual--full" style="margin:1rem 0 1.25rem;">
      <img
        src="{{ sg_full | image_url: width: 1200 }}"
        srcset="{{ sg_full | image_url: width: 600 }} 600w, {{ sg_full | image_url: width: 1200 }} 1200w, {{ sg_full | image_url: width: 1600 }} 1600w"
        sizes="(min-width: 990px) 900px, 100vw"
        alt="{{ sg_full_alt | escape }}"
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
        width="{{ sg_full.width }}"
        height="{{ sg_full.height }}"
        style="width:100%;max-width:100%;height:auto;border:1px solid var(--color-line, #e8e0dc);border-radius:10px;display:block;"
      >
    </figure>
  {%- endif -%}

  <h3>1. Chest</h3>
  <p>
    Measure around the fullest part of your bust while wearing the bra you would normally wear with this garment. Keep the tape horizontal and do not pull too tight.
  </p>
  {%- if sg_chest != blank -%}
    {%- assign sg_chest_alt = sg_chest.alt | default: 'Chest measurement diagram' -%}
    <figure style="margin:0.75rem 0 1.25rem;">
      <img
        src="{{ sg_chest | image_url: width: 800 }}"
        srcset="{{ sg_chest | image_url: width: 400 }} 400w, {{ sg_chest | image_url: width: 800 }} 800w, {{ sg_chest | image_url: width: 1200 }} 1200w"
        sizes="(min-width: 900px) 480px, 100vw"
        alt="{{ sg_chest_alt | escape }}"
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
        width="{{ sg_chest.width }}"
        height="{{ sg_chest.height }}"
        style="width:100%;max-width:520px;height:auto;border:1px solid var(--color-line, #e8e0dc);border-radius:10px;display:block;"
      >
      <figcaption style="font-size:0.82rem;margin-top:0.35rem;">Chest</figcaption>
    </figure>
  {%- endif -%}

  <h3>2. Waist</h3>
  <p>Measure around your natural waist — the narrowest part of your torso, just below your rib cage.</p>
  {%- if sg_waist != blank -%}
    {%- assign sg_waist_alt = sg_waist.alt | default: 'Waist measurement diagram' -%}
    <figure style="margin:0.75rem 0 1.25rem;">
      <img
        src="{{ sg_waist | image_url: width: 800 }}"
        srcset="{{ sg_waist | image_url: width: 400 }} 400w, {{ sg_waist | image_url: width: 800 }} 800w, {{ sg_waist | image_url: width: 1200 }} 1200w"
        sizes="(min-width: 900px) 480px, 100vw"
        alt="{{ sg_waist_alt | escape }}"
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
        width="{{ sg_waist.width }}"
        height="{{ sg_waist.height }}"
        style="width:100%;max-width:520px;height:auto;border:1px solid var(--color-line, #e8e0dc);border-radius:10px;display:block;"
      >
      <figcaption style="font-size:0.82rem;margin-top:0.35rem;">Waist</figcaption>
    </figure>
  {%- endif -%}

  <h3>3. Hips</h3>
  <p>
    Measure around the widest part of your hips. Do not wear shapewear, even if you would normally wear it with the garment. Keep the tape level all the way around.
  </p>
  {%- if sg_hips != blank -%}
    {%- assign sg_hips_alt = sg_hips.alt | default: 'Hips measurement diagram' -%}
    <figure style="margin:0.75rem 0 1.25rem;">
      <img
        src="{{ sg_hips | image_url: width: 800 }}"
        srcset="{{ sg_hips | image_url: width: 400 }} 400w, {{ sg_hips | image_url: width: 800 }} 800w, {{ sg_hips | image_url: width: 1200 }} 1200w"
        sizes="(min-width: 900px) 480px, 100vw"
        alt="{{ sg_hips_alt | escape }}"
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
        width="{{ sg_hips.width }}"
        height="{{ sg_hips.height }}"
        style="width:100%;max-width:520px;height:auto;border:1px solid var(--color-line, #e8e0dc);border-radius:10px;display:block;"
      >
      <figcaption style="font-size:0.82rem;margin-top:0.35rem;">Hips</figcaption>
    </figure>
  {%- endif -%}

  <h3>4. Garment length — skirts</h3>
  <p>Measure from the center of your waist down the front of the skirt to the desired length.</p>

  <h3>5. Garment length — dresses, tops, blouses, jackets</h3>
  <p>Measure from the point where your neck meets your shoulder down the front of the garment to the hem.</p>

  <p>
    <strong>Glazur tip:</strong> If you’re unsure about your size, contact us at
    <a href="mailto:{{ mail | escape }}">{{ mail | escape }}</a> — we’re happy to help you find your perfect fit.
  </p>
</div>
